title: Store Venjetinden
text:
Store Venjetinden (or sometimes "Store Vengetinden") is a <a href="mountain">mountain</a> in the municipality of <a href="Rauma%2C%20Norway">Rauma</a> in <a href="M%C3%B8re%20og%20Romsdal">Møre og Romsdal</a> county, <a href="Norway">Norway</a>. It is located about northeast of the mountain <a href="Romsdalshornet">Romsdalshornet</a>, about east of the <a href="Rauma%20%28river%29">Rauma</a> river and <a href="European%20route%20E136">European Route E136</a>, and about southeast of the town of <a href="%C3%85ndalsnes">Åndalsnes</a>. It is the highest summit in the <a href="Romsdalsalpane">Romsdalsalpane</a> range.
The first ascent was via the northeast ridge in 1881 by <a href="William%20Cecil%20Slingsby">William Cecil Slingsby</a> and Johannes Vigdal. The first ascent via the western ridge was in 1930 by Erik Heen and Karl Oshaug.
